=Description=
   
The Association of Amazonian Universities - UNAMAZ is a network of research and higher education institutions which promotes academic, scientific, technological and cultural cooperation between universities in eight countries of the Continental Amazon. During the past 22 years, its goal has been to consolidate itself as a high-level organization, able to meet the needs of training in higher education and the promotion and creation of knowledge that contribute to the welfare of the inhabitants of the Pan-Amazonian countries. 



